article.headline: Fullerton State 75, Colgate 68
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Bobby Brown scored 21 points and Jermaine Harper added 15, as Cal State Fullerton toppled Colgate 75-68 in the consolation game of the Mohegan Sun Classic Saturday. Hardy Asprilla added 13 points and a career-high 14 rebounds for the winners. Jon Simon led all scorers with 24 points for Colgate. The Titans from the Big West Conference started well. Brown scored 18 of his team's 43 points in the first half. He was 6-8 from the floor, including 4-6 on threes. This followed a 2-11 shooting and five points in a 69-57 first-round loss to Samford Friday night. The Titans (1-1) twice led by as many as 13 points in the first half. Colgate (0-2), a member of the Patriot League, rallied to reduce the first deficit (30-17) to 33-28 late in the half. But Cal State Fullerton answered, outscoring Colgate 10-2 to lead 43-30 at halftime. In addition to Brown, the Titans were ahead because of some sturdy man-to-man, which limited Colgate to 32 percent shooting (8-25). The Titans had shot 50 percent (15-30). Colgate competed well to close deficit to 71-66 with just over two minutes left. But Cal State Fullerton played some stout man-to-man defense to secure the victory. Colgate shot 40 percent for the game (20-50).
